  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, the evidence strongly suggests that growing the NADES-specific dataset used for the fine-tuning process would render a larger impact and enable much more efficient improvement of the algorithm without the need for costly and energy-inefficient computational resources.",
    "As a further note; the predictive power of this model can be improved through the accumulation of more data, and the model itself can be used to optimize the process.",
    "Through the process of bench-testing the model's predictions and thereby increasing the amount of available training data, the model will inevitably become more accurate through subsequent rounds of training.",
    "Techniques to optimize this process, known as Active Learning, typically rely on bench testing either the least-confident predictions (i.e.",
    "those predictions that lie very close to the chosen 0.5 threshold for stability), on a maximally diverse group of test cases, or a combination of these."
